These are the steps required to configure and implement the Advanced Management Edition modules. The manufacturing modules are integrated with the distribution, finances, and CRM modules. For example: *Sales Orders create demand for and consume production. *Purchase Orders provide supply to production. *Inventory items are used to define the bills of materials for the products produced. Production orders consume and produce inventory. *Inventory items are used in estimates and the product configurator. *Estimates and product configurations can be used in CRM opportunities, sales quotes, sales orders, and production orders.
Production transactions generate financial transactions indirectly through the Inventory module or directly in production management.{br}
You should review the [HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\config_InvMgmt_Basic_GeneralInfo|Order Management with Inventory Configuration: General Information] topic as a part of implementing manufacturing.{br}
Additionally, refer to [HelpRoot_Manufacturing\config_MFG_General_Settings_GeneralInfo|System Preparation for Manufacturing Implementation: General Information]. ==Manufacturing Checklists== The following checklists are the mandatory and optional configuration steps for a successful implementation. Your Acumatica ERP license indicates which functionality you have.[anchor|#_8913c90f-e353-4193-bdac-bdef9fa5d4d7] *Inventory **[HelpRoot_Manufacturing\config_MFG_General_Settings_Implem_Checklist|System Preparation for Manufacturing Implementation: Implementation Checklist] *Core Manufacturing functionality **[HelpRoot_Manufacturing\AM_BOM_Checklist|Bill of Material: Implementation Checklist] **[HelpRoot_Manufacturing\AM_PM_Checklist|Production Management: Implementation Checklist] **[HelpRoot_Manufacturing\AM_MRP_Checklist|MRP: Implementation Checklist] *Optional Manufacturing functionality **[HelpRoot_Manufacturing\AM_EST_CheckList|Estimating: Implementation Checklist] **[HelpRoot_Manufacturing\AM_PC_CheckList|Product Configurator: Implementation Checklist]

